com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel

Interface GIModuleConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GIHasContainer, GIHasParameterAccessFunctions, GIModelObject, IViewedModelObject

    @NotThreadSafe
 @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface GIModuleConfiguration
extends GIHasContainer
    Base interface of bswmd model module configuration.

    All method parameters must be non-null unless documented otherwise.

    • Method Detail

      • getArDefinitionSchemaVersion

        @PublishedMethod
IVersion getArDefinitionSchemaVersion()
        Returns the AUTOSAR schema version the currently referenced module definition of this GIModuleConfiguration.

        If no module definition is referenced or if no version is specified there, this method throws a GeneratorPackageInitializationException exception.

        Returns:
        The AUTOSAR schema version of the module definition xml file
        Throws:
        BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException -
        • If no module definition is referenced or if no version is specified there.

      • getBswImplementationArVersion

        @PublishedMethod
IVersion getBswImplementationArVersion()
        Returns the AUTOSAR version of the referenced BSW-implementation.

        If no BSW-implementation is referenced or if no version is specified there, this method throws a BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException exception.

        Returns:
        The AR version of the referenced BSW-implementation.
        Throws:
        BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException -
        • If no BSW-implementation is referenced or if no version is specified there.

      • getBswImplementationSwVersion

        @PublishedMethod
IVersion getBswImplementationSwVersion()
        Returns the SOFTWARE version of the referenced BSW-implementation.

        If no BSW-implementation is referenced or if no version is specified there, this method throws a BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException exception.

        Returns:
        The SOFTWARE version of the referenced BSW-implementation.
        Throws:
        BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException -
        • If no BSW-implementation is referenced or if no version is specified there.
